    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based, <strong>hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a matching lid, with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Chop your <strong>leek[s]</strong> in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and slice finely</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-prosciutto-and-leek-mac-n-cheese/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once hot, tear your <strong>prosciutto </strong>into the pan and cook for 4-5 min or until crisp</p><p>Remove 1/3 of the <strong>crispy prosciutto </strong>from the pan and set aside for garnish</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-prosciutto-and-leek-mac-n-cheese/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sliced leek </strong>into the pan with the crispy proscuitto with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Cook for 2 min or until starting to soften</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-prosciutto-and-leek-mac-n-cheese/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Grate your <strong>lighter cheese </strong>finely</p><p>Combine the <strong>grated lighter cheese</strong> with your<strong> cornflour</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>floured cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-prosciutto-and-leek-mac-n-cheese/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the leek is starting to soften, add your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong>, <strong>soft cheese</strong>, 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml] </span><strong>milk</strong> and 400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[520ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[680ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>and stir it all together</p><p>Add your <strong>pasta</strong>,<strong> floured cheese </strong>and a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and mix it all together</p><p>Nestle the pasta into the water as much as you can and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-prosciutto-and-leek-mac-n-cheese/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cover with a lid and put the dish in the oven for 20-25 min or until the pasta is cooked through</p><p>Tip: Give everything a stir halfway through for evenly cooked pasta!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-prosciutto-and-leek-mac-n-cheese/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your<strong> spinach </strong>and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Once the pasta is cooked, remove the dish from the oven and add <strong>half </strong>of your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>and the <strong>spinach </strong>and stir until it starts to wilt</p><p>Top with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>and the <strong>reserved</strong> <strong>crispy prosciutto</strong></p><p>Return the dish to the oven and cook, uncovered, for 4-5 min further or until the cheese has melted \u2013 this is your <strong>one pot prosciutto & leek mac 'n' cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-prosciutto-and-leek-mac-n-cheese/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>one pot prosciutto & leek mac 'n' cheese</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>chives</strong> roughly over with<strong> </strong>scissors</p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
